<HEADLINE>
FT  23 DEC 93 / Lecturers threaten strike on contracts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN AUTHERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Talks between principals of further education colleges and the Natfhe
lecturers' union over new contracts broke up yesterday, John Authers writes.
Natfhe said it would ballot members on holding a national strike in the new
year. Mr Geoff Woolf, general secretary, said proposals over the length of
the working year had proved the sticking point. Under draft contracts from
the employers annual holiday leave would be halved.
The College Employers' Forum said it was willing to continue negotiations
before December 31, but only if Natfhe changed its position on the working
year.
Mr Gordon Scott, forum chairman, said that under the terms of the colleges'
budget Pounds 50m in grant would be withheld if flexible contracts were not
introduced. Natfhe's proposals were not sufficiently flexible to gain the
extra grant.
</TEXT>
