<HEADLINE>
FT  23 DEC 93 / Middlesbrough FC plans new stadium
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Middlesbrough Football Club is to move from its turn-of-the-century ground
at Ayresome Park to a new Pounds 16m, 32,000-seat stadium alongside the
River Tees.
The move is needed to fulfil the all-seater stipulation of the Taylor report
into football ground safety and is part of the regeneration of Middlesbrough
Dock. The Teesside Development Corporation said it was the largest
relocation, in capacity terms, in the history of the Football League.
