FT  22 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Further pay-out at Atlantic
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Total liabilities of Atlantic Computer Systems, the leasing company that
collapsed in April 1990, should not exceed Pounds 168m, the liquidators said
yesterday.
With net realisations of up to Pounds 39.2m under current estimates, that
could lead to a further dividend of 4p in the pound after an interim payment
announced this week of 19p.
Mr Richard Boys-Stones, one of the liquidators from Price Waterhouse, the
accountants, said the payment reflected his strategy of 'maximising the
realisations and minimising the liabilities'.
The recalculated liabilities figure contrasts sharply with the estimate of
nearly Pounds 450m provided by Atlantic's directors at the time it went into
administration.
