FT  22 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Art market shows big sales rise
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTONY THORNCROFT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The international art market improved significantly in 1993 judging by
figures from Sotheby's and Christie's, the world's leading auction houses.
Sotheby's registered sales during the year of Dollars 1.32bn (Pounds 879m),
a 17 per cent gain in dollar terms and 31 per cent in sterling.
Business improved in the autumn, with sales of Dollars 833m ,a 24 per cent
improvement in dollars and 32 per cent in sterling.
Christie's reported 1993 sales figures of Dollars 1.1bn ,a 14 per cent
sterling rise and a 3 per cent gain in dollars during the year.
Its business also picked up in the autumn, with a turnover of Dollars 531m
(Pounds 357m), 14 per cent better in sterling but a 9 per cent improvement
in dollars, the international currency of valuable works of art.
