FT  22 DEC 93 / Observer: Hairline crack
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Is Vladimir Zhirinovsky showing signs of losing his hair?
The question is not as daft as it sounds if one supports the analysis of
humorist Vladimir Voynovich, quoted in Solovyov and Klepikova's recent
biography of Boris Yeltsin.
Since Lenin's time, bald and hairy rulers have alternated throughout Russian
history: Lenin (bald), Stalin (hairy), Khruschev (bald), Brezhnev (hairy),
Andropov (bald), Chernenko (hairy), Gorbachev (bald), Yeltsin (hairy).
So the message seems to be that as long as Zhirinovsky keeps his hair on, we
should be all right.
</TEXT>
