FT  22 DEC 93 / Housing 'set for further recovery'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The housing market has been subdued over recent weeks but is poised for
further recovery next year, a survey by the Royal Institution of Chartered
Surveyors of more than 120 estate agents has found, Andrew Taylor writes.
The institution said: 'Buyers were nervous in the run up to last month's
Budget and the market - in spite of some flurries of activity - remains
quiet in the approach to Christmas.' Although the market had improved in
1993 it was still being held back by too many sellers asking high prices.
Almost 85 per cent of agents reported that prices had remained static in the
past three months. Another 10 per cent reported price falls with just over 5
per cent reporting price increases.
