In a legal assault meant to enforce the European Union's single market, the
European Community said yesterday it would take member countries to court in
184 cases where they have failed to implement EU legislation, AP-DJ reports
from Brussels.
The offensive reverses an 11-month truce between the Commission, which is
responsible for upholding Community rules, and member states which have been
slow to take in Community laws to national legislation.
